    <p>K-pop, short for Korean pop music, is a genre originating from South Korea known for its catchy tunes, impressive choreography, and visually appealing music videos. It features a diverse range of musical styles, blending pop, hip-hop, R&B, and electronic dance music. The global popularity of K-pop has given rise to dedicated fan communities and played a key role in promoting Korean culture worldwide.</p>
